PREP: Cook pasta according to package directions; rinse with cold water and drain well. In large bowl, combine pasta, romaine, mozzarella, Romano cheese, olives and pepper; toss to mix. Cover and chill. Meanwhile, heat grill to medium. COOK: CLEAN. Wash hands. Grill chicken over medium heat 6 minutes; turn chicken over. Brush with 3 tablespoons salad dressing. Grill 5 to 7 minutes longer or until internal juices run clear. (Or insert instant-read meat thermometer in thickest part of chicken. Temperature should read 170 degrees F.) Remove from grill. Brush with 3 tablespoons salad dressing. SERVE: Toss salad with remaining dressing; place on 4 serving plates. Slice chicken breasts and arrange evenly over salad. Serve with hot focaccia bread, if desired. CHILL: Refrigerate leftovers immediately.